## Directory Structure
```
src/
  components/   # React UI components
  api/          # Express route handlers
  utils/        # Shared utilities
  types/        # TypeScript type definitions
tests/          # Test files (Jest)
```

## Coding Conventions
- Use async/await (no raw callbacks or .then chains)
- All React components must have TypeScript props interfaces
- API responses follow `{ data, error, message }` format
- Use named exports (not default exports) for components
- Write tests for all new utility functions

## Key Patterns
- Auth: JWT tokens in httpOnly cookies, use `renewSession()` to refresh
- DB: All queries go through `src/utils/db.js` query helper
- Error handling: Use `AppError` class from `src/utils/errors.js`
- API routes: `/api/v1/[resource]` pattern

## Known Gotchas
- `refreshToken()` does NOT exist — use `renewSession()` instead
- Never call the DB directly — always use the db utility
- The `UserService` class is a singleton, don't re-instantiate it

